de.mrapp.android.adapter

Interface NoChoiceListAdapter<DataType>

  • Type Parameters:
    DataType - The type of the adapter's underlying data
    All Superinterfaces:
    android.widget.Adapter, java.lang.Cloneable, DataStructure, EnableStateListAdapter<DataType>, FilterableListAdapter<DataType>, ItemStateListAdapter<DataType>, android.widget.ListAdapter, Loggable, Parameterizable, RecyclerViewAdapter, Restorable, java.io.Serializable, SortableListAdapter<DataType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    NoChoiceListAdapterImplementation

    public interface NoChoiceListAdapter<DataType>
extends ListAdapter<DataType>
    Defines the interface, an adapter, whose underlying data is managed as a list of arbitrary items, which can not be selected, must implement. Such an adapter's purpose is to provide the underlying data for visualization using a AbsListView widget.
    Since:
    0.5.0
